books.title: To Kill a Mockingbird
books.author: Harper Lee
books.description: A novel about the serious issues of rape and racial inequality, set in the 1930s American South.

books.author: George Orwell
books.description: A dystopian social science fiction novel and cautionary tale about the dangers of totalitarianism.

books.title: The Great Gatsby
books.author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
books.description: A story about the young and mysterious millionaire Jay Gatsby and his quixotic passion for the beautiful Daisy Buchanan.

books.title: Moby Dick
books.author: Herman Melville
books.description: An epic tale of the voyage of the whaling ship Pequod and its captain, Ahab, who is obsessed with pursuing the giant white whale Moby Dick.

books.title: Pride and Prejudice
books.author: Jane Austen
books.description: A romantic novel that charts the emotional development of the protagonist, Elizabeth Bennet, who learns the error of making hasty judgments.
